publicationXrefc96.standardName: Screening of High-Yield 2-Phenylethanol Producing Strain from Wild-Type Saccharomyces cerevisiae and Optimizationof Fermentation Parameters.

comments.content:
Metabolic pathway of 2-Phenylethanol production in microorganisms.
Wild-typeSaccharomyces cerevisiae is capable of producing 2-PE through both the shikimate and Ehrlich metabolic routes.
This was created with reference to the following figure:
[figure 2](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12294199/)
